National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and MOTEGI Toshimitsu, Secretary General of the Liberal Democratic Party of Japan, met to discuss the regional security environment and U.S.-Japan relations. They emphasized the importance of strengthening bilateral economic and security cooperation, supporting Ukraine in its defense against Russia's invasion, and increasing multilateral cooperation in the region, including with South Korea. Sullivan mentioned that President Biden is looking forward to meeting Prime Minister Kishida at the G7 Leaders' Summit in Hiroshima. Both officials committed to further deepening the bilateral partnership to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific.